And as an honerable mention in terms of art/story/character {{champion:48}}, his gameplay update was fine, but for me, his reworke was a horrible loss of an interesting character.

Though all in all the better question would be which reworked champ i **don't** miss...for me, most reworks failed so far. The either imo failed to capture the previous champ properly, resulting in a maybe great new champ but therefor a pure loss regardeing the old one, or they failed to actually change anything meaningfull, resulting in exactly the same issues that basically caused the rework so the rework was basically pointless, or story and art fail for me...The only reworks i'm really happy with are  Sion and Anivia so far, and the once that i'm failry happy with are Poppy, WW and Brand

{{champion:43}}  number one, I feel like they remove her before she could shine. Claim she need gold to play support remove her then add support item. She can't lane against the meta poke mages, assassin mage soon follow. She would of stomp them. 

